sweeten /ˈswiːtən/

1. V-T If you sweeten food or drink, you add sugar, honey, or another sweet substance to it. 使变甜 

例： He liberally sweetened his coffee. 他在咖啡里加了大量的糖。 

2. V-T If you sweeten something such as an offer or a business deal, you try to make someone want it more by improving it or by increasing the amount you are willing to pay. (通过改善条件或提高价格等) 使 (报价或交易等) 更有诱惑力 

例： Kalon Group has sweetened its takeover offer for Manders. 卡隆集团已经在其收购曼德斯的报价上加了些好处。

